message.content: One of the most significant events that happened in Norway in the past 20 years is the terrorist attacks that occurred on July 22, 2011. This tragic event, carried out by a Norwegian right-wing extremist named Anders Behring Breivik, involved a bombing in Oslo and a mass shooting on the island of Utøya. A total of 77 people were killed, mostly young people attending a summer camp organized by the Norwegian Labour Party's youth organization. This event had a profound impact on Norway, leading to discussions on security, extremism, and the country's values of openness and tolerance.
